  "why": "DeepHunter is designed to discover generic erroneous behaviours (misclassifications and prediction inconsistencies) produced by metamorphic mutations and coverage-guided exploration, not to steer generation toward attacker-chosen, specific target outputs. The paper defines an error as a change in model prediction (Definition 2) or a mismatch between original and quantized model predictions (Definition 3), and the framework keeps \"failed tests which are incorrectly predicted by the DNN\" (Section 3.1). The experiments and evaluation report counts and diversity of unique errors and coverage improvements (e.g., Tables 3–6, RQ3), with no mechanism, objective, or evaluation for inducing a predefined attacker-chosen target label or other attacker-specified outputs. Therefore the fuzzer performs untargeted exploration that reveals generic failures rather than targeted attack discovery.",
